article.description: — Lance Jones scored 14 points and Southern Illinois defeated Illinois State 59-49 on Sunday.
article.headline: Jones carries S. Illinois over Illinois St. 59-49
article.linkText: Jones carries S. Illinois over Illinois St. 59-49
article.story: CARBONDALE, Ill. -- — Lance Jones scored 14 points and Southern Illinois defeated Illinois State 59-49 on Sunday. Steven Verplancken Jr. had 12 points for Southern Illinois (10-9, 4-9 Missouri Valley Conference) and Kyler Filewich scored 11. Verplancken's 3-pointer with 14:45 before halftime gave the Salukis a 14-12 lead and they never trailed again. Josiah Strong scored 14 points for the Redbirds (6-15, 3-12) and Antonio Reeves 10. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
